1. d4 e6 2. Nc3 Nf6 (2... f5? { Not recommended in this move order } 3. e4!) 3. Bf4 (3. e4 d5 { Transposes back into a French! Be sure to review this study: https://lichess.org/study/mr9g4cVe }) 3... Bb4 { This is already territory that most Jobava London players won't be so familiar with. Black has ideas to immediately pressure the center like c5, Qa5, Ne5, and also Nd5 (since black hasn't committed the pawn to d5). } 4. a3 (4. e3 Nd5!? { [%csl Rf4,Rc3] } (4... c5 { also possible } { [%cal Gd8a5,Gf6e4] })) 4... Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 b6 6. Nf3 Bb7 7. e3 Ne4 8. c4 d6 { black gets the nice harmonious Dutch Attack setup. } { [%cal Gb8d7,Gf7f5] } *


