{ Video analysis: https://youtu.be/STwcmr-nIBo }
1. e4 (1. h3) 1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. d3 f5 { The start of the Lucchini Gambit. While this is objectively dubious, there is certainly some hidden beauty in this variation... } { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gf7f5] } 5. Ng5 { A natural looking move (and also one of Stockfish's top suggestions) which aims to refute this opening right away. This has occurred in over 200 games on lichess. On the surface, it looks like black is in trouble. However, it is white who is about to fall into immense danger! } 5... f4! { Cutting off the dark-squared bishop's eye on the knight and threatening Qxg5. While is allows Nf7 or Bf7+, black has some deep ideas in mind... } { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gf5f4] } 6. Nf7 Qh4 7. g3 { [%csl Gf2] } (7. O-O? Nf6 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gf6g4] } 8. Nxh8 (8. Nd2 b5! { Crazy move! Stockfish gives black a small edge, but this requires further analysis! }) 8... Ng4) 7... Qh3 8. Nxh8 (8. c3 d5 9. exd5 b5!! { Another highly chaotic variation! } 10. Bb3 (10. Bxb5 Kxf7 11. Bxc6 Bg4 12. Qb3 Nf6 13. d6+ Be6 14. Qb5 Bxd6 $17) 10... Kxf7 11. dxc6+ Kf8 $17 { [%cal Gc8g4] }) (8. Kd2 { engine move -- deserves maybe some more analysis } 8... Qg2) 8... d5!! { After extensive analysis, it appears black is winning after this earth-shattering move } { [%csl Gd5][%cal Ge4d5] } 9. Bxd5 (9. exd5 Nd4 10. c3 Bg4 11. Qa4+ Kf8 (11... Bd7 12. Qd1 Bg4) 12. cxd4 { [%csl Rc5,Rg3][%cal Gd4c5,Gf4g3] } 12... fxg3 13. dxc5 gxf2+ 14. Kd2 Qg2 15. Kc3 Qxh1 16. Nd2 Qe1 17. d4 Qe3+ 18. Bd3 (18. Kb4 a5+ 19. Kb5 Qxd4 { [%csl Gd7,Gb6][%cal Gg4d7,Gc5c6,Gd4b6,Gb6b5] }) 18... e4 { [%cal Gd2f1] } 19. Nxe4 Qxd3+ (19... f1=Q) 20. Kxd3 f1=Q+ 21. Kc3 Qf3+ { [%cal Gc3d2] } 22. Kc4 (22. Kd2 Re8 { [%cal Ge8e2] }) 22... Qxe4) 9... Bg4 10. f3 (10. Qd2 Nd4 $19 { [%csl Gg2,Gg4,Gd4,Gc5,Gh3,Rc1,Rb1,Ra1,Rh1,Rd5,Rh8][%cal Gh3g2,Gg4d1,Gd4c2,Gd4f3] }) 10... fxg3 11. fxg4 g2 { [%csl Gg2,Gg1][%cal Gg2h1,Gc5g1] } 12. Bxc6+ bxc6 13. Ke2 g1=N+ { [%cal Gg1e2] } 14. Rxg1 (14. Qxg1 Bxg1 15. Rxg1 Qxh2+ 16. Kf1 O-O-O) 14... Qxh2+ { [%csl Gf2][%cal Gh2f2] } *


