1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. d3 f5 5. exf5?! { 2nd most common move on lichess (played 269 times) } 5... d5 { The most natural move-- gaining and a tempo on the bishop and threatening to recapture on f5. This is much like a reverse King's Gambit Accepted. } 6. Bb5 { critical line - white pins the knight and threatens to capture on e5. Amazingly, black can gambit another pawn... } 6... Ne7 7. Nxe5 O-O { despite being down 2 pawns (temporarily) black is doing quite well! With better development and the guarantee to win the f5 pawn, there is great compensation for the slight material deficit } 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. Ba4 Nxf5 $17 *


