1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. d3 f5 5. O-O { The most simple and likely the best approach for white } 5... Nf6 6. Nc3 (6. Ng5 { Is interesting, but nothing special for white } 6... Qe7! { Neither Nf7 nor Bf7 will do much harm. Engine gives close to equality but perhaps more analysis can be done }) 6... d6 7. Bg5 Na5!? { Attempting to remove the white's pesky light-squared bishop so black can castle and live happily ever after } { [%csl Rg8,Rc4][%cal Ga5c4,Rc4g8,Ge8g8] } 8. Bxf6! { slightly unnatural (3rd most common move on lichess), but Stockfish's top choice for concrete reasons. The following variation is a complicated engine line where it looks like white maintains a clear edge. } (8. Nd5 { Most played move on lichess (71 games) } 8... Nxc4 9. dxc4 c6 10. Nxf6+ gxf6 11. Bh6 { Out of 8 games on lichess this has been played in all 8. However, Bh6 is a clear mistake.. } 11... f4! $17 { [%csl Rh6][%cal Gd8e7,Gh8g8,Gc8g4] }) 8... Qxf6 9. Nd5! { A multipurpose move generating multiple threats! } { [%csl Rf6,Rc5,Ra5,Rc7][%cal Gd5f6,Gb2b4,Gb4c5,Gb4a5,Gd5b4,Gd5c7] } 9... Qd8 10. b4 Nxc4 11. bxc5 fxe4 12. dxc4 exf3 13. Qxf3 Be6 14. Rad1 $16 *


