1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bc4 { The beginning of the Boden-Kieseritzky Gambit. White invites black to capture on e4 which could easily lead to a reverse Stafford Gambit } 3... Nxe4 (3... Nc6 { Transposes into a Two Knights Defense }) 4. Nc3 Nxc3 5. dxc3 { The main position of the Boden-Kieseritzky Gambit Accepted. White is down a pawn, but has better development and lots of tactical potential especially if black isn't careful. See the next chapters for further analysis } *


