1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Nbd7 5. e3 (5. cxd5 exd5 { Will likely transpose }) 5... c6 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bd3 Be7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. O-O Re8 10. Qc2 Nf8 { The beginning of a typical maneuver. Black plans to to get the bishop pair with Ng6, Bd6, and h6. } 11. Rab1 { A typical idea-- white plans to launch a minority attack with b4, a4, and b5 } 11... Ng6 12. b4 a6 { Slowing down the minority attack } 13. a4 Bd6 14. b5 axb5 15. axb5 h6 16. Bxf6 Qxf6 17. e4 { Looks like black is in trouble, but.... } 17... Nf4!! { a brilliant resource } 18. e5 Qe6 19. exd6 Qg4 20. Ne1 Rxe1 21. f3 Rxf1+ 22. Bxf1 Qe6 $17 { Upon winning d6, black will be up a clean pawn } *


