1. e4 { [%clk 1:30:58] } 1... e5 { A small surprise } { [%clk 1:29:42] } (1... c5 { I was mainly expecting my opponent to play Sicilian in this game. }) 2. Nf3 { [%clk 1:30:52] } 2... Nc6 { [%clk 1:30:04] } 3. Nc3 { [%clk 1:30:41] } 3... Nf6 { [%clk 1:30:13] } 4. a3 { A tricky sideline, I enjoyed playing several years ago. } { [%clk 1:30:42] } 4... d5 { The most principled reply } { [%clk 1:28:03] } 5. Bb5 { [%clk 1:30:49] } 5... Nxe4 { [%clk 1:27:54] } 6. Qe2 { [%clk 1:31:03] } 6... Qd6 { [%clk 1:26:45] } 7. Nxe4 { [%clk 1:30:54] } 7... dxe4 { [%clk 1:27:09] } 8. Qxe4 { [%clk 1:31:21] } 8... Bd7 { [%clk 1:27:09] } 9. d4 { [%clk 1:31:18] } 9... O-O-O { This is one of the most solid lines for black } { [%clk 1:26:35] } 10. dxe5 { [%clk 1:24:59] } 10... Nxe5 { [%clk 1:23:43] } 11. Bxd7+ { [%clk 1:24:42] } (11. Nxe5?? { a funny line... } 11... Qd1+!! 12. Kxd1 Bg4+ 13. Ke1 Rd1#) 11... Rxd7 { [%clk 1:14:37] } 12. O-O { [%clk 1:23:56] } 12... Nxf3+ { [%clk 1:14:49] } 13. Qxf3 { [%clk 1:24:18] } 13... Qd5 { [%clk 1:14:22] } 14. Qxd5 { [%clk 1:20:10] } 14... Rxd5 { [%clk 1:14:39] } 15. Be3 { I offered a draw here, but my opponent wanted to play on. Not much happened for the rest of the game... } { [%clk 1:20:00] } 15... Bc5 { [%clk 1:11:20] } 16. Rad1 { [%clk 1:13:35] } 16... Rhd8 { [%clk 0:58:00] } 17. Rxd5 { [%clk 1:12:34] } 17... Rxd5 { [%clk 0:58:25] } 18. Bxc5 { [%clk 1:11:53] } 18... Rxc5 { [%clk 0:58:52] } 19. Rc1 { [%clk 1:12:12] } 19... a5 { [%clk 0:57:16] } 20. Kf1 { [%clk 1:10:25] } 20... a4 { [%clk 0:57:04] } 21. Ke2 { [%clk 1:10:15] } 21... Rb5 { [%clk 0:56:30] } 22. Rb1 { [%clk 1:10:23] } 22... Kd7 { [%clk 0:55:26] } 23. Kd3 { [%clk 1:08:34] } 23... Kd6 { [%clk 0:54:27] } 24. b3 { [%clk 1:04:55] } 24... axb3 { [%clk 0:52:51] } 25. cxb3 { [%clk 1:04:00] } 25... Rd5+ { [%clk 0:52:32] } 26. Kc3 { [%clk 1:03:23] } 26... Rc5+ { [%clk 0:51:49] } 27. Kd3 { [%clk 1:03:25] } 27... Rh5 { [%clk 0:52:03] } 28. h3 { [%clk 1:02:37] } 28... Rg5 { [%clk 0:52:25] } 29. g3 { [%clk 1:00:53] } 29... Rd5+ { [%clk 0:52:47] } 30. Ke3 { [%clk 0:58:57] } 30... Re5+ { [%clk 0:47:39] } 31. Kd3 { [%clk 0:59:05] } 31... Rd5+ { Draw agreed. Solid game, but maybe a bit boring for the viewers (sorry!). Thankfully, I was able to save all the Sicilian prep I did for a future opponent (see round 8). } { [%clk 0:47:39] } *


