1. Nf3 { After the dry draw in round 5, I wanted to avoid another king's pawn game and decided to play the Reti. I went into this game hoping for a long and interesting fight, and that's exactly what I got... } { [%clk 1:30:57] } 1... d5 { [%clk 1:26:05] } 2. e3 { [%clk 1:31:10] } 2... Nf6 { [%clk 1:24:36] } 3. c4 { [%clk 1:31:20] } 3... e6 { [%clk 1:24:53] } 4. Nc3 { [%clk 1:31:29] } 4... Be7 { [%clk 1:23:19] } 5. b3 { [%clk 1:31:43] } 5... dxc4 { [%clk 1:23:22] } 6. Bxc4 { [%clk 1:30:35] } 6... c5 { [%clk 1:22:29] } 7. Bb2 { [%clk 1:29:58] } 7... Nc6 { [%clk 1:21:56] } 8. O-O { [%clk 1:26:39] } 8... O-O { [%clk 1:21:45] } 9. Qc2 { [%clk 1:21:41] } 9... b6 { [%clk 1:05:47] } 10. d4 { [%clk 1:17:10] } 10... cxd4 { [%clk 1:06:54] } 11. Rad1 { [%clk 1:16:49] } 11... Bb7 { [%clk 0:45:58] } 12. Nxd4 { [%clk 1:13:26] } 12... Qc8 { [%clk 0:44:16] } 13. Nce2 { [%clk 1:05:50] } 13... Nb4 { I completely missed this idea when I played Nce2. Thankfully white can hold on... } { [%clk 0:36:28] } 14. Qb1 { [%clk 1:03:13] } 14... Be4 { [%clk 0:34:10] } 15. Qa1 { [%clk 1:00:11] } 15... e5 { At first this move looks quite strong, but it's actually a mistake. } { [%clk 0:32:47] } 16. a3 { [%clk 0:47:01] } (16. Nf3! Bxf3 17. gxf3 Qh3 18. Bxe5 Qxf3 19. Ng3 $14 { Even though the kingside looks weakened, white is doing quite well with the bishop pair. }) 16... exd4 { [%clk 0:28:09] } 17. axb4 { [%clk 0:47:12] } 17... dxe3 { [%clk 0:23:18] } 18. Ng3 { [%clk 0:46:16] } 18... Qc6 { [%clk 0:14:37] } (18... exf2+ 19. Rxf2 { Even though white lost a pawn, it seems like there's a ton of compensation }) 19. Nxe4 { [%clk 0:44:03] } 19... Qxe4 { [%clk 0:14:39] } 20. Rde1 { [%clk 0:41:56] } 20... Bd6 { [%clk 0:05:08] } 21. Rxe3 { [%clk 0:39:41] } 21... Qf4 { [%clk 0:05:00] } 22. Rg3 { [%clk 0:37:54] } 22... Nh5 { [%clk 0:04:20] } 23. Bxg7 { [%clk 0:34:31] } 23... Nxg3 { [%clk 0:04:41] } 24. fxg3 { [%clk 0:34:20] } 24... Qg5 { [%clk 0:03:32] } 25. Bxf8 { [%clk 0:22:49] } (25. Bf6 { The engine's choice which is apparently much stronger. This was difficult to calculate and evaluate. } 25... Qg6 26. Qd1 $18 { only winning move } { [%cal Gd1d6,Gc4d3] }) 25... Rxf8 { [%clk 0:03:48] } 26. Qxa7 { [%clk 0:23:04] } 26... b5 { [%clk 0:01:59] } 27. Bd3 { [%clk 0:16:30] } (27. Bxf7+ { Engine line... } 27... Kh8 28. Qd4+ Be5 29. Qc5 Kg7 30. Bc4 Rxf1+ 31. Bxf1) 27... Bxb4 { [%clk 0:01:56] } 28. Kh1 { [%clk 0:16:36] } 28... Bc5 { [%clk 0:00:55] } 29. Qd7 { [%clk 0:14:36] } 29... b4 { [%clk 0:00:48] } 30. Bf5 { [%clk 0:12:05] } (30. Bxh7+!! { Didn't even consider this } 30... Kxh7 31. Rf4 $18 Be7) 30... Qe7 { [%clk 0:00:51] } 31. Qd3 { [%clk 0:10:09] } 31... h6 { [%clk 0:00:59] } 32. Qc4 { [%clk 0:09:48] } 32... Qe3 { [%clk 0:00:43] } 33. Bb1 { [%clk 0:09:10] } 33... Kg7 { [%clk 0:00:38] } 34. Qc2 { [%clk 0:07:13] } 34... f5 { [%clk 0:00:44] } 35. Qd1 { [%clk 0:06:43] } 35... Qd4 { [%clk 0:00:33] } 36. Qf3 { [%clk 0:05:16] } 36... Qe3 { [%clk 0:00:35] } 37. Qd5 { [%clk 0:04:13] } 37... Qd4 { [%clk 0:00:52] } 38. Qe6 { [%clk 0:03:55] } 38... Rf6 { [%clk 0:00:59] } 39. Qc8 { [%clk 0:04:02] } 39... Rf8 { [%clk 0:01:08] } 40. Qb7+ { [%clk 0:02:35] } 40... Rf7 { [%clk 0:01:31] } 41. Qf3 { [%clk 0:02:47] } 41... Qe3 { [%clk 0:29:34] } 42. Qh5 { [%clk 0:31:15] } 42... Qg5 { [%clk 0:09:33] } 43. Qd1 { [%clk 0:31:10] } 43... Qg4 { [%clk 0:09:33] } 44. Qc2 { [%clk 0:29:16] } 44... Qd4 { [%clk 0:09:40] } 45. g4 { [%clk 0:24:22] } 45... Qc3 { [%clk 0:07:53] } 46. gxf5 { [%clk 0:22:09] } 46... Qxc2 { [%clk 0:08:18] } 47. Bxc2 { [%clk 0:22:35] } 47... Kf6 { [%clk 0:08:00] } 48. Bd3 { [%clk 0:22:16] } 48... Re7 { [%clk 0:08:12] } 49. g3 { [%clk 0:21:46] } 49... Re3 { [%clk 0:08:27] } 50. Bc4 { [%clk 0:19:19] } 50... Re5 { [%clk 0:08:28] } 51. Be6 { [%clk 0:14:59] } 51... Re2 { [%clk 0:07:58] } 52. Rc1 { [%clk 0:15:24] } 52... Bd4 { [%clk 0:07:31] } 53. Rc6 { [%clk 0:14:14] } 53... Rf2 { [%clk 0:06:35] } 54. Bc8+ { [%clk 0:13:25] } 54... Kf7? { [%clk 0:06:03] } (54... Kg7 { puts up more resi