{ Hey Eric, I've been watching some of your games and I would like to know what is the logic behind a very common move that you play with the Sicilian. After 1e4 c5 2Nf3, you go for e6, insted of the "main line" 2...d6, which makes sense for me. It is preparing Nf6, and without d6, White can harass my Knight with e5. But 2...e6 I don't know what it does... }
