1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d3 Nc6 4. Nf3 Bc5 5. c3 a6 { a useful (and high level)
idea in this opening to retreat the bishop to a7 before deciding how to
complete development } 6. Bb3 Ba7 7. O-O d6 8. Nbd2 O-O 9. Re1 { perhaps not the
best move because of black's idea } (9. h3) 9... Ng4! 10. Re2 Kh8! 11. h3 Nh6 12. Nf1 f5 13. Bxh6 gxh6 14. exf5 Bxf5 { black has succeeded in opening the
g and f files! With the king safely tucked away on h8, the position is ripe
for attack } 15. N1h2 Qf6 16. Qd2 Rae8 17. Kh1 Re7! { because g8 is off limits,
adams plans to maneuver the rook to g7 } 18. a3 Rg7 19. Rg1 h5 20. Ba2 Bd7 21. b4 Ne7 22. d4 exd4 23. cxd4 Ng6 24. Re4 Nf4 25. h4 Bc6 26. d5 Bb5 27. g3 Nh3 28. Rg2 Bf1 { 0-1 White resigns. } (28... Nxf1 29. Qxf3) 0-1


